    <h2 id="h2-pokemon"><strong>Pokemon</strong></h2>
    <p id="p-pokemon">One of my favorite video game series is Pokemon.</p>
    <ul>
    <li id="main-li"><strong>Favorite Versions:</strong></li>
      <li>
        <ul>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">Crystal</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">Emerald</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">Fire Red</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">Platnum</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">Soul Silver</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="main-li"><strong>Challenges:</strong></li>
      <li>  
        <ul>
          <li>Hardcore Nuzlockes</li>
          <li>
            <ul>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">Hardcore Nuzlockes are a normal playthrough of a pokemon game except with the following self-imposed rules:</li>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You can only catch one pokemon per location such as a route, city, or cave</li>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You can only catch one pokemon per evolution line</li>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You are not allowed to level up your pokemon over the highest level pokemon that the upcoming gym leader has</li>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">The game must be set to "set" mode</li>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You are not allowed to use items in battle except for pokeballs and held items</li>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">If a pokemon faints, it is considered dead and cannot be used for the remainder of the run</li>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">If you white-out in a battle, the run is considered a lost and you have to reset the game completely</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li id="main-li"><strong>Kaizo Ironmon</strong></li>
      <li>
        <ul>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">A kaizo ironmon is a much harder version of a hardcore nuzlocke as it contains the following rules</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You can only catch one pokemon per location such as a route, city, or cave</li>
          <li>
	        <ul>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">If you choose to catch the pokemon you must commit to that pokemon</li>
              <li id="pokemon-sub-li">This means you can't use your previously caught pokemon, just that one pokemon</li>
            </ul id="pokemon-sub-li">
	       </li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You are only allowed one pokemon in your party</li>
          <li>
	        <ul>
              <li>The only exception to this rule is if the other pokemon in your party are used for HM moves, used to progress through the story</li>
              <li>These pokemon cannot be used in battle</li>
            </ul>
	      </li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">Once you enter a location, you may not leave that location until you beat all the trainers in that location</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You can't return to that location unless the in game story requires you to</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">The following must be randomized</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">
            <ul>
              <li>Pokemon Base Stats</li>
              <li>Pokemon Move learnsets</li>
              <li>Pokemon Encounter Locations</li>
              <li>Starter Pokemon</li>
              <li>Opponent's Pokemon</li>
              <li>Items</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You must select your starter pokemon randomly</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You can't use any pokemon with a total base stat greater than 599</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You can't heal outside of battle other than the use of pokemon centers</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">You can't use in-game shops unless you are buying pokeballs or repels</li>
          <li id="pokemon-sub-li">Game is set to set mode</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
